
[Richmond, 30 Nov. 1780. Etienne Charavay, comp., Inventaire des autographes et documents historiques runis par M. Benjamin Fillon, Paris, 1878, i, item 295, lists a letter signed by TJ of this date, 2 p. folio, and summarizes it as follows: Il mande que le pouvoir excutif a lintention de placer, dans les principaux forts, quatre canons pour protger les vaisseaux qui sont dans les ports de lEtat. Letter not found, and addressee not identified. It is possible, however, that the letter here described was a copy of TJs letter to Benjamin Harrison of [172] this date, for the description closely parallels the first sentence of the second paragraph of that letter.]
